verbose_text: The results showed that the liver is the major organ and hepatocytes are the major cells involved in rIL-10 gene expression, while rIL-10 serum levels markedly increased following the transfer for 8 h. High levels of rIL-10 were sustained for at least 1 week in the serum and hepatocyte, while the rIL-10 mRNA expression in liver was sustained for 2 weeks following a single injection, which is in agreement with a previous study.
